AU  - Wiederholt, Mirko
T1  - Business Cycle Dynamics under Rational Inattention
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdv027
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 82
IS  - 4
SP  - 1502
EP  - 1532
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We develop a dynamic stochastic general equilibrium (DSGE) model with rational inattention and compare its predictions to data. Households and decision-makers in firms have limited attention and optimally allocate their attention. Rational inattention is the only source of slow adjustment. The model matches the empirical impulse responses to monetary policy shocks and aggregate technology shocks. At the same time, profit losses and utility losses from inattention are very small. Furthermore, it matters whether one uses this model or a conventional DSGE model for policy analysis.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdv027
ER  - 



